Definition: feminine of {{h3064}}; Jehudijah, a Jewess; Jehudijah.
perhaps from a form corresponding to {{h3061}}; Judaistic; Jehdai, an Israelite; Jehdai.
a briefer form of one corresponding to {{h3061}}; Jehud, a place in Palestine; Jehud.
denominative from a form corresponding to {{h3061}}; to Judaize, i.e. become Jewish; become Jews.
from {{h3051}}; properly, what is given (by Providence), i.e. a lot; burden.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3051}}; deliver, give, lay,   prolong, pay, yield.
a primitive root; to give (whether literal or figurative); generally, to put; imperatively (reflexive) come; ascribe, bring, come on, give, go, set, take.
contraction for {{h3068}}, and meaning the same; Jah, the sacred name; Jah, the Lord, most vehement. Compare names in '-iah,' '-jah.'
from {{h3068}} and {{h270}}; Jehovah-seized; Jehoachaz, the name of three Israelites; Jehoahaz. Compare {{h3099}}.
from {{h3068}} and {{h1931}}; Jehovah (is) He; Jehu, the name of five Israelites; Jehu.
feminine of {{h3039}}; beloved; Jedidah, an Israelitess; Jedidah.

from {{h3045}} and {{h410}}; knowing God; Jediael, the name of three Israelites; Jediael.
from {{h1811}}; tearful; Jidlaph, a Mesopotamian; Jidlaph.

a primitive root; to know (properly, to ascertain by seeing); used in a great variety of senses, figuratively, literally, euphemistically and inferentially (including observation, care, recognition; and causatively, instruction, designation, punishment, etc.); acknowledge, acquaintance(-ted with), advise, answer, appoint, assuredly, be aware, (un-) awares, can(-not), certainly, comprehend, consider, × could they, cunning, declare, be diligent, (can, cause to) discern, discover, endued with, familiar friend, famous, feel, can have, be (ig-) norant, instruct, kinsfolk, kinsman, (cause to let, make) know, (come to give, have, take) knowledge, have (knowledge), (be, make, make to be, make self) known,   be learned,   lie by man, mark, perceive, privy to, × prognosticator, regard, have respect, skilful, shew, can (man of) skill, be sure, of a surety, teach, (can) tell, understand, have (understanding), × will be, wist, wit, wot.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3045}}; certify, know, make known, teach.
from {{h3045}}; knowing; Jada, an Israelite; Jada.
from {{h3045}} and {{h3050}}; Jah has known; Jedajah, the name of two Israelites; Jedaiah.
from {{h3045}}; properly, a knowing one; specifically, a conjurer; (by impl) a ghost; wizard.
from {{h3034}}; praised; Jiddo, an Israelite; Iddo.

a primitive root; used only as denominative from {{h3027}}; literally, to use (i.e. hold out) the hand; physically, to throw (a stone, an arrow) at or away; especially to revere or worship (with extended hands); intensively, to bemoan (by wringing the hands); cast (out), (make) confess(-ion), praise, shoot, (give) thank(-ful, -s, -sgiving).
from {{h3045}}; knowing; Jaddua, the name of two Israelites; Jaddua.
from {{h3034}}; thankful; Jadon, an Israelite; Jadon.
from the same as {{h1706}}; perhaps honeyed; Jidbash, an Israelite; Idbash.
of uncertain derivation; Jidalah, a place in Palestine; Idalah.
from {{h3039}}; properly, affection; concretely, a darling object; dearly beloved.
a primitive root; (compare {{h3034}}); properly, to handle, i.e. to throw, e.g. lots; cast.
from the same as {{h1730}}; loved; amiable, (well-) beloved, loves.
or יְדֻתוּן; or יְדִיתוּן; probably from {{h3034}}; laudatory; Jeduthun, an Israelite; Jeduthun.

(Aramaic) from a word derived from an unused root (meaning to gather) and a derivation of a root corresponding to {{h7717}}; heap of the testimony; Jegar-Sahadutha, a cairn East of the Jordan; Jegar-Sahadutha.

a primitive word; a hand (the open one [indicating power, means, direction, etc.], in distinction from {{h3709}}, the closed one); used (as noun, adverb, etc.) in a great variety of applications, both literally and figuratively, both proximate and remote [as follows]; (  be) able, × about,   armholes, at, axletree, because of, beside, border, × bounty,   broad, (broken-) handed, × by, charge, coast,   consecrate,   creditor, custody, debt, dominion, × enough,   fellowship, force, × from, hand(-staves, -y work), × he, himself, × in, labour,   large, ledge, (left-) handed, means, × mine, ministry, near, × of, × order, ordinance, × our, parts, pain, power, × presumptuously, service, side, sore, state, stay, draw with strength, stroke,   swear, terror, × thee, × by them, × themselves, × thine own, × thou, through, × throwing,   thumb, times, × to, × under, × us, × wait on, (way-) side, where,   wide, × with (him, me, you), work,   yield, × yourselves.
feminine of {{h3019}}; fatigue; weariness.
a primitive root; to fear; be afraid, fear.
from {{h3021}}; earnings (as the product of toil); that which he laboured for.
from {{h3021}}; tired; hence (transitive) tiresome; full of labour, weary.
from {{h1540}}; exiled; Jogli, an Israelite; Jogli.

(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3027}}; hand, power.

from {{h3068}} and {{h251}}; Jehovah-brothered; Joach, the name of four Israelites; Joah.

from {{h3068}} and {{h8199}}; Jehovah-judged; Jehoshaphat, the name of six Israelites; also of a valley near Jerusalem; Jehoshaphat. Compare {{h3146}}.

a form of {{h3089}}; Jehoshabath, an Israelitess; Jehoshabeath.
from {{h3068}} and {{h1}}; Jehovah-fathered; Joab, the name of three Israelites; Joab.

from {{h1986}} (in the sense of hardness); a precious stone, probably onyx; diamond.
from {{h1984}} and {{h410}}; praising God; Jehallelel, the name of two Israelites; Jehalellel, Jehalelel.

from {{h1431}} and {{h3050}}; magnified of Jah; Jigdaljah, an Israelite; Igdaliah.
feminine from {{h1361}}; hillock; Jogbehah, a place East of the Jordan; Jogbehah.
from {{h3009}}; a plowed field; field.
probably from {{h1481}}; a lodging; Jagur, a place in Palestine; Jagur.
from {{h3025}}; fearful; afraid, fearest.
from {{h3013}}; affliction; grief, sorrow.
a primitive root (probably rather the same as {{h3013}} through the common idea of dissatisfaction); to push away; be removed.
from {{h3021}}; tired; weary.
from {{h3021}}; toil; hence, a work, produce, property (as the result of labor); labour, work.

from {{h3201}}; potent; Jehukal, an Israelite; Jehucal. Compare {{h3116}}.
from {{h3068}} and {{h5068}}; Jehovah-largessed; Jehonadab, the name of an Israelite and of an Arab; Jehonadab, Jonadab. Compare {{h3122}}.
from {{h3068}} and {{h5414}}; Jehovah-given; Jehonathan, the name of four Israelites; Jonathan. Compare {{h3129}}.

from {{h3068}} and {{h7650}}; Jehovah-sworn; Jehosheba, an Israelitess; Jehosheba. Compare {{h3090}}.
from {{h1350}}; avenger; Jigal, the name of three Israelites; Igal, Igeal.

from {{h3001}}; dry ground; dry (ground, land).
from the same as {{h1314}}; fragrant; Jibsam, an Israelite; Jibsam.

a primitive root; to be ashamed, confused or disappointed; also (as failing) to dry up (as water) or wither (as herbage); be ashamed, clean, be confounded, (make) dry (up), (do) shame(-fully), × utterly, wither (away).
from {{h3001}}; dry; dried (away), dry.
